results.abstract: ashes buried in Kremlin wall; party, Govt and scientific leaders laud his work as spacecraft designer

headline.main: Chief Soviet Space Designer Is Buried in Kremlin

results.snippet: MOSCOW, Jan. 18 The chief designer of the Soviet space program, Sergei P. Korolev, a figure cloaked in anonymity until his death last Thursday at age 59, was given a state funeral in snow-swept Red Square today.

byline.original: By THEODORE SHABAD Special to The New York Times

headline.main: SOVIET SHOWROOM OPERATES IN CITY; Gift Service Part of Drive to Earn More Dollars

results.snippet: A showroom for Soviet automobiles, motorcycles, television sets, cameras, watches, clothing and other goods is operating here as part of an accelerating drive by Moscow to earn foreign currency.
